      <p>A "sought after" aircraft fuel and service center at a Northern California general-aviation airport. The business holds a ground lease whose permitted uses are broad — ground &amp; flight school, aircraft maintenance &amp; repair, parts sales, charter &amp; rental, avionics upgrades, and aircraft management — indicating an established, multi-decade FBO footprint. Ownership entity not disclosed; confirm via California Secretary of State.</p>
      <p><strong>Timeline:</strong> Year unknown — FBO established on a ground lease. Nov 8 2023 — listed on DealStream by BTI Group. Nov 1 2024 — listing renewed (still unsold ~1 year later). 2026-05-21 — still listed; financials shown remain the Jan–Oct 2023 period.</p>
      <p><strong>Leadership:</strong> "Fully staffed" with management that "will stay" post-sale. Whether a non-owner general manager runs day-to-day operations is not disclosed.</p>
